1. If someone enters the room, then the number of killers in the room remains the same. So, there were three killers in the room before the person entered, and there are still three killers in the room after the person enters.

2. Nobody leaves the room, so the number of killers does not change. Therefore, there were three killers in the room before anyone entered, and there are still three killers in the room after the person enters.
